The paper discusses algorithms for interactive machine learning, specifically in the context of learning from random counter-examples. This falls under the broad category of machine learning, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions applications such as classification and clustering, which are covered by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the algorithms, which is a topic covered by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
